==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*augan-'' ‘eye’, from Indo-European ''*okw-'' ‘see’.

Cognates include Old High German [[ouga]] (German [[Auge]]), Old Saxon ''ōga'' (Dutch [[oog]]), Old Norse [[auga]] (Swedish [[öga]], Danish [[øje]]), Gothic [[𐌰𐌿𐌲𐍉]].  The IE root was also the source of Greek [[ὤγψ]] ‘eye’, Latin [[oculus]] ‘eye’, Avestan ''aši'' ‘the eyes’, Old Slavic ''oko'' (Russian [[око]]).

